cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a model for multi-hop reading comprehension, which is a task in natural language processing. The model uses three modules to explore, propose, and assemble information from multiple documents to answer a question. This falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The model also involves optimization and machine learning techniques, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the model uses a tree structure to represent divergent reasoning chains, which is a concept that can be related to neural networks (cs.NE).
